### Firestore Security Rules Workflow
- Whenever a new feature modifies the database structure, adds new fields, or changes user data access patterns, you must automatically evaluate the current Firestore Security Rules.
- If the rules need to be updated, provide the full, production-ready rules text inside a markdown code block (similar to the schema with isValidAppData() we used).
- Include brief step-by-step instructions on where to paste and publish them in the Firebase Console.

GLOBAL RULE: This app is localized. NEVER hardcode text. Always add new strings to `src/translations.ts` and use the LanguageContext. All UI elements must support both RTL and LTR layouts.
GLOBAL RULE: User-generated content (categories/descriptions) uses async API translation via `src/services/translationService.ts` with caching. Never hardcode user-content translations; always resolve through LanguageContext and respect `keepOriginalValues`.